  }}&lt;/ref&gt; The racial makeup of the county was 57.5% white, 17.2% black or African American, 13.9% Asian, 0.4% American Indian, 0.1% Pacific islander, 7.0% from other races, and 4.0% from two or more races. Those of Hispanic or Latino origin made up 17.0% of the population.&lt;ref name=&quot;census-dp1&quot;/&gt; In terms of ancestry, 10.7% were [[German Americans|German]], 9.6% were [[Irish Americans|Irish]], 7.9% were [[English Americans|English]], 4.9% were [[Italian Americans|Italian]], 3.5% were [[Russian Americans|Russian]], 3.1% were [[Polish Americans|Polish]], 2.9% were [[American ancestry|American]] and 2% were [[French Americans|French]].&lt;ref name=&quot;census-dp2&quot;&gt;{{cite web |url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/10_5YR/DP02/0500000US24031 |title=Selected Social Characteristics in the United States 2006-2010; American Community Survey; 5-Year Estimates |id=DP02 |access-date=January 22, 2016 |publisher=United States Census Bureau |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213033010/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/10_5YR/DP02/0500000US24031 |archive-date=February 13, 2020 |url-status=dead}}&lt;/ref&gt; 8.1% of Montgomery County was of [[Central America]]n descent, with [[Salvadoran Americans]] constituting 5.4% of the county's population. Over 52,000 people of Salvadoran descent lived in Montgomery County, with Salvadoran Americans comprising approximately 32% of the county's Hispanic and Latino population. 3.8% of the county is of [[South America]]n descent, with [[Peruvian Americans]] being the largest South American community constituting 1.2% of the county's population.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web |url=https://www.census.gov |title=Hispanic or Latino by Type: 2010 |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |access-date=August 7, 2017 |df=mdy-all }}&lt;/ref&gt;

Of the 357,086&amp;nbsp;households, 35.7% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 53.4% were married couples living together, 11.3% had a female householder with no husband present, 31.4% were non-families, and 25.0% of all households were made up of individuals. The average household size was 2.70 and the average family size was 3.22. The median age was 38.5 years.&lt;ref name=&quot;census-dp1&quot;/&gt;

The median income for a household in the county was $93,373 and the median income for a family was $111,737. Males had a median income of $71,841 versus $55,431 for females. The per capita income for the county was $47,310. About 4.0% of families and 6.0% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 7.2% of those under age 18 and 6.3% of those age 65 or over.&lt;ref name=&quot;census-dp3&quot;&gt;{{cite web |url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/10_5YR/DP03/0500000US24031 |title=Selected Economic Characteristics – 2006-2010; American Community Survey; 5-Year Estimates |id=DP03 |access-date=January 22, 2016 |publisher=United States Census Bureau |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213031517/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/10_5YR/DP03/0500000US24031 |archive-date=February 13, 2020 |url-status=dead}}&lt;/ref&gt;

===2014 estimates===
The [[United States Census Bureau]] estimated the county's population was 1,030,447 as of 2014.&lt;ref name=census2014&gt;{{cite web |work= State &amp; County Quickfacts |title= Montgomery County, Maryland |publisher= United States Census Bureau |url= http://quickfacts.census.gov/qfd/states/24/24031.html |access-date= August 11, 2015 |url-status= dead |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20110606163928/http://quickfacts.census.gov/qfd/states/24/24031.html |archive-date= June 6, 2011 |df= mdy-all }}&lt;/ref&gt; If it were a city, it would be the [[List of United States cities by population#United States|tenth most populous city]] in the U.S. after [[San Jose, California]] and [[Austin, Texas]].

The ethnic makeup of the county was estimated to be the following in 2013:&lt;ref name= census2014/&gt;

*62.6% [[White American|White]] (47.0% [[Non-Hispanic White]])
*18.6% [[African American|Black]]
*14.9% [[Asian American|Asian]]
*0.7% [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]]
*0.1% [[Native Hawaiian]] or [[Pacific Islander American|Pacific Islander]]
*3.1% [[Multiracial American|Two or more races]]

In addition, 18.3%  were [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]], of any race.&lt;ref name= census2014/&gt;

People who were born on continent of [[Africa]] are 6% of the county's total residents. The plurality of these were born in [[Ethiopian American|Ethiopia]].&lt;ref name= african&gt;&quot;[https://www.montgomerycountymd.gov/partnerships/community/african.html African Community] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171211160943/https://www.montgomerycountymd.gov/partnerships/community/african.html |date=December 11, 2017 }}&quot;. ''Office of Community Partnerships''. Montgomery County Government. 2013. Retrieved February 28, 2018.&lt;/ref&gt; People from [[Chinese American|China]] are the fastest-growing immigrant population in the county; people from Ethiopia are the county's second-fastest growing immigrant population.&lt;ref name= african/&gt;

